title: Gila Cliff Dwellings National Monument: Amphibians
body: Explore This Park    Learn About the Park     Nature     Animals     Amphibians                Amphibians         Bullfrog quietly watching, Middle Fork. NPS Photo by Barry Nielsen  Amphibians found in the Gila National Forest include: Tiger salamander (Ambystoma tigrinum) New Mexico spadefoot toad (Scaphiopus multiplicatus) Woodhouse's toad (Bufo woodhousii) Southwestern toad (Bufo microscaphus) Red-spotted Toad (Bufo punctatus) Western Chorus Frog (Pseudacris triseriata) Mountain treefrog (Hyla eximia) Canyon treefrog (Hyla arenicolor) Bullfrog (Rana catesbeiana) Chiricahua Leopard Frog (Rana chiricahuensis) Lowland Leopard Frog (Rana yavapaiensis) Checklist for Fish, Amphibians, Reptiles and Mammals
